        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### Q9: Robust Prediction (8 pts)\n",
        "\n",
        "HireVision needs to predict salaries for new graduates who may have incomplete or unusual profiles. Write a function that handles three real-world edge cases:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. **Missing features (3 pts):** Some keys in `new_grad` may be `None` or absent entirely. Impute numeric features with the median from `training_data`. For missing categorical features, use all-zeros for that variable's one-hot columns (same as unseen category).\n",
        "2. **Unseen category (3 pts):** A new graduate’s category value (e.g., `college_type='International'`) may not exist in the training data. Encode as all-zeros for that variable’s one-hot columns.\n",
        "3. **GPA scale mismatch (2 pts):** If `gpa > 10`, assume it’s on a percentage scale and divide by 10 (e.g., 85 → 8.5)."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "GI51HdSYo-ua"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def predict_salary(model, feature_columns, training_data, new_grad):\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Predict salary for a new graduate, handling edge cases.\n",
        "\n",
        "    Args:\n",
        "        model:          fitted XGBRegressor\n",
        "        feature_columns: list of feature names the model expects\n",
        "        training_data:  DataFrame used for training (one-hot encoded columns\n",
        "                        like 'gender_Female', 'gender_Male' — NOT raw categoricals)\n",
        "        new_grad:       dict with graduate attributes (may have missing/unusual values)\n",
        "\n",
        "    Returns:\n",
        "        float: predicted starting_salary_lpa (NOT log — exponentiate the prediction)\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "\n",
        "    import pandas as pd\n",
        "\n",
        "    # -----------------------------\n",
        "    # Create empty row with all features = 0\n",
        "    # -----------------------------\n",
        "    row = pd.Series(0, index=feature_columns, dtype=float)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # -----------------------------\n",
        "    # Handle numeric features\n",
        "    # -----------------------------\n",
        "    numeric_features = ['gpa', 'internships', 'english_score', 'work_experience_months', 'skills_certifications']\n",
        "\n",
        "    for col in numeric_features:\n",
        "        val = new_grad.get(col, None)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Missing → median imputation\n",
        "        if val is None:\n",
        "            if col in training_data.columns:\n",
        "                val = training_data[col].median()\n",
        "            else:\n",
        "                val = 0\n",
        "\n",
        "        # GPA scale fix\n",
        "        if col == 'gpa' and val is not None and val > 10:\n",
        "            val = val / 10\n",
        "\n",
        "        if col in row.index:\n",
        "            row[col] = val\n",
        "\n",
        "    # -----------------------------\n",
        "    # Handle categorical features (one-hot)\n",
        "    # -----------------------------\n",
        "    categorical_vars = ['gender', 'city_tier', 'college_type', 'field', 'parental_education']\n",
        "\n",
        "    for var in categorical_vars:\n",
        "        val = new_grad.get(var, None)\n",
        "\n",
        "        if val is None:\n",
        "            continue  # leave all zeros\n",
        "\n",
        "        col_name = f\"{var}_{val}\"\n",
        "\n",
        "        # If category exists → set 1\n",
        "        if col_name in row.index:\n",
        "            row[col_name] = 1\n",
        "        # Else unseen → leave all zeros (handled automatically)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # -----------------------------\n",
        "    # Convert to DataFrame\n",
        "    # -----------------------------\n",
        "    X_new = pd.DataFrame([row])\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Ensure column order\n",
        "    X_new = X_new[feature_columns]\n",
        "\n",
        "    # -----------------------------\n",
        "    # Predict (log → level)\n",
        "    # -----------------------------\n",
        "    log_pred = model.predict(X_new)[0]\n",
        "    salary_pred = np.exp(log_pred)\n",
        "\n",
        "    return float(salary_pred)"
      ]
    },
